Package neuroEvo

Class GenomeNet

java.lang.Object
neuroEvo.GenomeNet
public class GenomeNet
extends java.lang.Object
This class contains the Genetic code of all current Genomes
This class handles nearly everything from the forward propagation process to the actual algorithm that governs breeding and mutating
Author:
Caleb Devon
Created 7/11/2021

      protected int searchForGlobalEqual​(Gene test)
      This method searches if a Gene has existed in the population's past
      Parameters:
      test - Gene to search for equivalent
      Returns:
      Returns the innovation number of the equivalent gene, or -1 if no equivalences exist

    • getGeneByGlobalInnov

      protected Gene getGeneByGlobalInnov​(int innovNum, boolean node)
      Gets a gene from the global list by it's innovation number
      Parameters:
      innovNum - Innovation Number to search for in the global list
      node - True if searching for a NodeGene, false if searching for a ConnectionGene
      Returns:
      The Gene that matches the Innovation Number being searched for (null if none exist)

    • crossover

      protected GenomeNet crossover​(GenomeNet g2, int generation)
      Breeding method which will create a mix of the Genetic Code of 2 parents to create a child
      Parameters:
      g2 - The second parent for use in breeding (this Genome will be the first)
      generation - Pass the generation to use in the Child Genome declaration
      Returns:
      Returns the Child Genome produced by the Gene mixing of the 2 parents
